column2: STUDENT TEACHING IN HEALTH AND PHYSICAL EDUCATION
column4: ITEC 19525 and EPSY 29525; and Official valid certification of Child Safety Training, approved Basic Life Support and A.L.I.C.E. Training must be presented to the campus office of clinical experience or designated faculty/staff at Regional campuses as prerequisite for student teaching.
column6: Full time student teaching which includes a balanced experience in elementary and secondary health and physical education.
